<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ881007-0019 </DOCNO><HL> Technology Brief -- Ford Motor Co.: Aerospace Subsidiary Signs $394.3 Million Intelsat Pact </HL><SO> </SO><CO> F FORGN </CO><IN> ARO </IN><TEXT>   Ford Motor Co.'s Ford Aerospace Corp. unit has signed a $394.3 million contract to build five communications satellites for the International Telecommunications Satellite Organization.    When the contract was awarded last month, Intelsat said Ford could earn as much as $130 million additionally over the next 10 years if the satellites met the group's performance standards.    Intelsat provides satellite services that beam telephone calls and television signals between countries. </TEXT></DOC>